trackname: Psalm For The Elks Lodge Last Call
lyrics: Let the waitress put the chairs up\mLet the glasses that you broke\mForm a picture of our leader\mWith a halo made of smoke\mLet the golden oldies station crackle and come through\mWith a final benediction we'll hum along to\mBefore we say goodnight\mLet our talk about the ball game\mAnd the weather show we care\mLike a sound we didn't notice\mUntil it stopped and left us there\mWith the traffic and our heartbeats beating in straight time\mLet our hatred and affection march in the same line\mBefore we say goodnight\mOh protect our secret handshake \monce more, with feeling\mLet the toast to absent members push through the ceiling\mBefore we say goodnight

So you watch the sunrise sinking and she's talking in her sleep\mA dream of how alone she was tomorrow when you keep\mAll those promises to someone in a mirror you will find\mAt your parents' house in 1989\mTerrorized\mBy the ruling party, calendars and commas\mSmall request\mCould we please turn around\m and around and around?\mTurn around\mSo you whisper your arrival walking backwards to the door\mWonder briefly what it is you're hesitating for\mAll the streets lie down, deserted in the darkest part of night\mTo lead you through the evening to the light\mPulled along\mIn the tender grip of watches and ellipses\mSmall request\mCould we please turn around and around and around?\mTurn around

[Recorded Voice]\mYou are listening to the heartbeat of the Sage\mSage posses the newest and most revolutionary advance in split-second presentation\mAs well as split-second calculation\mTo protect the future of America\mThe defense techniques of tomorrow had to be discovered now\mBut Sage needed more than this\mNew concepts, new tools, new weapons\mBy analyzing the past, Sage can project into the future\m[Sage Francis: Verse I]\mI used to think that rappers had it figured out\mBrass Monkey, St. Ides, Olde English, and Guinness Stout\mOnce a man, twice a boy with a choice of vice, a voice of spite\mNot enough poisons to pick to enjoy this life\mMan, I thought suicide was a suburban myth\mI couldn't see my own hands being the ones I'm murdered with\mThat is until I traveled this world a bit\mI understand now if I lose my nerve I'll get the girl to do it!\mShe heard the music but preferred the person--she's worth it\mThe only one I let behind the curtain to work with\mPushin' buttons and playin' with levers\mWe'll stay together as long as I'm modest in my songs\mRadio - suckers never play this\mScared shitless of dismissing Clear Channel playlists\mPoorly developed, yet highly advanced\mThe black music intertwined with a white man's line dance\m[Recorded Voice]\mSupersonic, super destructive, seemingly unresistable\mOn the job around the clock, with 24-hour-a-day reliability\mConstantly monitoring, pulse-taking, controlling\mInto a continuous flow of interpretations, which could be understood at a glance\m[Sage Francis: Verse II]\mIt's not lonely on top\mI'm kept busy with shivers and cold shakes\mSitting on snowbanks\mWaving to be delivered some soulmates\mSo I wait/weight\mLift and test my faith on several levels\mBuild my body till they send me an empty face with the head of devils\mMy breath resembles the smell of flowers\mYanked from life and placed in a vase\mSits and wilts and rots and dies in the name of grave mistakes\mThat we all make\mBelieve we're getting by treating ourselves wrong\mThrow me a reindeer John letter party\mAnd I'll be there with bells on\mHell spawned some iffy calls in City Hall\mThey still got the gall\mTo blame the vitriol on Biggie Smalls\mFrom strip malls\mTo strip clubs\mThey slip drugs\mInto the drinks that kids love\mTell us to drink up and get buzzed\mThis is the buzz kill, jump into the saddle\mEmerge from the dust kicked up in the uphill battle\mWith my guns drawn and sword out\mPointed towards the courthouse\mI sort out words from my war-torn mouth\mI disassociate the actions with their meanings\mOn some "ends justify the means" mentality\mPlus I'm bleeding\mGive me a Band-Aid, a band that can't play\mA fanbase with hearing aids and a voice like a hand grenade\mI pull the wool over their vision\mPull the pin and push it in 'em\mI'm using women as a pin cushion\mA supervillain\mWith some warpaint and jokes done in poor taste\mWe'll see who laughs last, all the way to foreign banks[Recorded Voice]\mReady to take over in a matter of seconds\mTo protect the future of America\mSage also has protection too\m(Come on, come on, feel it, feel it)\mThe protection which comes with the possesion of weapons of retaliation\mBut is this protection enough?\m[Sage Francis: Verse III]\m(I was) I was B-boyin' in my former body\mSinging all the songs at parties\mNow I'm like, "Don't let nobody\mThrough the door in the hotel lobby!"\mI'd wear Armani if they endorsed me\mSo people who are poor can rob me\mThen forcefully sex me up\mColor me confused when they paint issues black and white\mResuscitate their gray matter right back to life\mIt's my destiny, she wants me, she beckons\mShe left me for dead but Death didn't want no sloppy seconds\mI'm certified fresh\mI freedom-kiss the French for their political dissent\mLike mwah/moi\mI do it with tongue this time\mAnd take that bovine blood out your wine\mAnd take that statue back to the lab it was created at\mYour huddled masses yearning to breath free\mTake 'em back!\mYour homeless, tempest-tost to me\mTake 'em back!\mThe U-S-A has cracked[Recorded Voice]\mAnd as long as we're on guard\mAs long as we're ready to look ahead\mTo move ahead\mThe future of America is secure

They've said it every year but this times it seems like\mThe end is near\m \mand I'm in line to see the light\mHow far does this black tunnel go\mI got a car but the gas is running low\mAnd as long as I've known the bumps and creeks of this house\mIt's starting to make the types of sounds that only comes from people's mouths\mYou can't tell me it's still settling\mBuilt on an indian burial ground killing everything\mThe childhood scar on my chin is back again\mThat old jump over my own leg dance move has to end\mI've seen better days in my night terrors\mI was a bike messenger without a bike and I would write letters\mAsk directions to your whereabouts\mBefore the slow walk the rest of the show-offs were pealing out\mTo many hares only one tortoise\mThats why I left this city, too fast paced for this HO-HUM Taurus\mBy the time I developed the pictures\mThey're as blurry as my memory of constant life fixtures\mIf distance is a girl's best friend\mTell them bitches in the rough who think that love comes with diamonds\mSlave labor, you made me work for what I couldn't have\mDiamonds cut, but coal burns and nothing lasts forever\mWonder why I bothered saving any of your letters\mThey're just aged paper\mCrumble\mSlave labour, you made me work for what I couldn't have\mDiamonds cut, but coal burns and nothing lasts\mWonder why I saved your urn of ashes\mI've got an insecurity box for your mail\mTracing the name on the return adress as if it was made of braille\mPretended it was your finger but careful to not break a nail\mThe one that sealed the coffin shut when it opened caused a paper trail\mBut since then I buried your dead sea scrolls\mAnd emptied my head of these old trivial memories that I seem to hold\mNow you're a foot note with cement shoes\mIn case you wonder what that sinking feeling has been ever since I left you

You're neither here or there\mI swear I can't find you anywhere\mDamn sure you ain't in my closet,\m or under my rug\mThis love search is really making me bug\mAnd if you know who you are why don't you make yourself seen?\mTake the chance with my love and you'll find out what I mean\mFantasies can run, but they can't hide\mAnd when I find you I'm gon' pour all my love inside\m[Hook]\mI need love\mI need love[Verse 3]\mI wanna kiss you, hold you, never scold, you just love you\mSuck on you neck, caress you and rub you\mGrind, moan and never be alone\mIf you're not standing next to me you're on the phone\mCan't you hear it in my voice? I need love bad\mI've got money, but love's something I've never had\mI need your ruby red lips sweet face and all\mI love you more than a man who's 10 feet tall\mI'd watch the sunrise in your eyes\mWe're so in love when we hug we become paralyzed\mOur bodies explode in ecstasy unreal\mYou're as soft as a pillow and I'm as hard as steel\mIt's like a dream land, I can't lie, I never been there\mMaybe this is an experience that me and you can share\mClean and unsoiled yet sweaty and wet\mI swear to you this is something I'll never forget\m[Hook]\mI need love\mI need love\m[Verse 4]\mSee what I mean? I've changed, I'm no longer\mA playboy on the run, I need something that's stronger\mFriendship, trust, honor, respect, admiration\mThis whole experience has been such a revelation\mIt's taught me love and how to be a real man\mTo always be considerate and do all I can\mProtect you, you're my lady and you mean so much\mMy body tingles all over from the slightest touch\mOf your hand and understand I'll be frozen in time\mTill we meet face to face and you tell me you're mine\mIf I find you, girl, I swear I'll be a good man\mI'm not gonna leave it in destiny's hands\mI can't sit and wait for my princess to arrive\mI gotta struggle and fight to keep my dream alive\mI'll search the whole world for that special girl\mWhen I finally find you watch our love unfurl[Hook]\mI need love\mI need love\m[Outro]\mGirl, listen to me. When I be sitting in my room all alone, staring at the wall\mFantasies, they go through my mind, and I've come to realize that I need true love\mAnd if you wanna give it to me, girl, make yourself seen. I'll be waiting\mI love you

trackname: Waiting For The World To End
lyrics: [Intro]\mYeah\mIt's the God Rakim\mWord up, I'm blazin' this out to all my comrades\mYa know I mean?\mFrom the slums of New York, to the gutters all over the world\mThis is for y'all\m[Verse 1]\mThrough my travels, I try to take righteous steps\mBecause right or left could mean life or death\mNo matter how trife it get, my sights is set\mBut it's twice the threat when the nights is death\mMy mental windows refuse to close, they get exposed\mTo the neighborhood info where the poison wind blows\mA deadly plague spreadin' negativity, viciously\mUnto every city be in ghetto misery\mDon't let it get to me, the writer be left to die\mBut it get mesmerize if it catch your eye\mShine's enormous, from jewellery, vehicles and garments\mBut it's torment, jealousy, drug wars or warrents\mTallyin', slowly turnin' into barbarians\mMore scary when the whole boulevard's carryin'\mLivin' in the world of sin, my ghetto girls and men\mWaitin' for the world to end\m[Hook]\m"Tryin' to paint a perfect picture and excel"\m"In case you didn't know"\m"Never movin' backwards"\m"\mComplicated\m"\m"Know what I mean?"\m"Tryin' to paint a perfect picture and excel"\m"In case you didn't know"\m"Never movin' backwards"\m"Complicated"\m"Know what I mean?"\m[Verse 2]\mI see destruction, even little kids trust none\mThey bust guns, that's what they get a rush from\mWhen I see 'em, we build and have a real discussion\m"Yo Ra, what's the jewel of the day?" "What up, son?"\m"You got ambition?" Shorty said, "Man, listen\mI got demands for livin', can't stand division\mMake grands on my mission, 'til everythin' glisten\mWomen in the Expedition, no plans for prison\mIn a vision the city get, two milleni, G\mSittin' in my embassy, sippin' Hennesy\mGettin' high, and watch life pass me by"\mSo I asked him why, with a fast reply\mHe said, "I'm livin' just to die without any feelings\mSo I wait here for my maker 'til it's time to go\mWith this dime I know, with all of her girls and all of my men\mWaitin' for the world to end"[Hook]\m"Tryin' to paint a perfect picture and excel"\m"In case you didn't know"\m"Never movin' backwards"\m"Complicated"\m"Know what I mean?"\m"Tryin' to paint a perfect picture and excel"\m"In case you didn't know"\m"Never movin' backwards"\m"Complicated"\m[Verse 3]\mShorty was taught to keep his head to the sky, and never cry\mBut the streets left him to die, now it's death in his eye\mLivin' in sin'll give men a sinister grin\mFrom the beginnin' to end, in it to win\mEvil rebels, doin' what we do in the ghetto\mThinkin' if we was thorough we could deceive the devil\mYou can't win, your life'll end, try again\mShorty said, "Why we born again to die again?"\mThat's what I said when I realized I had a gift\mTo uplift and be one of Allah's advocates\mTeach the youth and speak the truth\mShow 'em what peace can do when they'll reach for you\mAnd my reward won't be jewels or cheese, it's even better\mI can be one of the greatest MC's ever\mIf I tell 'em they intelligent women and great men\mAnd live, stop waitin' for the world to end[Hook]\m"Tryin' to paint a perfect picture and excel"\m"In case you didn't know"\m"Never movin' backwards"\m"Complicated"\m"Know what I mean?"\m"I'm ragin'\m, \mrippin' up the stage an'\mDon't it sound amazin'\m, \mknow what I mean?"\m"\mDon't it sound amazin'\m, \mknow what I mean?"\m"Rakim"

trackname: In The Wee Small Hours Of The Morning
lyrics: In the wee small hours of the morning\mWhile the whole wide world is fast asleep\mYou lie awake and think about the girl\mAnd never even think of counting sheep\mWhen your lonely heart has learned its lesson\mYou'd be hers if only she would call\mIn the wee small hours of the morning\mThat's the time you miss her most\mWhen the sun is high in the afternoon sky\mYou can always find something to do\mBut from dusk till dawn as the clock ticks on\mSomething happens to you\mWhen your lonely heart has learned its lesson\mYou'd be hers if only she would call\mIn the wee small hours of the morning\mThat's the time you miss her most of all\mThat's the time you miss her most of all

trackname: To Love You All Over Again
lyrics: A qA quiet room is what you get, an empty glass, an unmade bed,\mA picture window with a view, and all I think about is you\mTo feel so bad, to feel so good, to let it be misunderstood,\mNow I long to lose my senses to love you all over again.\mThe shouted words, the tired sighs, the traded kiss of sad goodbyes,\mThe living off of our desires, then putting out a thousand fires:\mTo feel so bad, to feel so good, to let it be misunderstood,\mNow I'd tear down my defenses to love you all over again.\mTo know a place without regret, you make believe you paid your debt\mBut in that clean and quiet room you can't believe it's over yet.\mOut on a lark, at home asleep, the endings play, the bands retreat\mBut in that dumb luck of the few, the consolation comes to you:\mTo feel so bad, to feel so good, the verdict's in ? it's understood\mI will be tried for my offenses and love you all over again.

trackname: What Do You Hear in These Sounds
lyrics: I don't go to therapy to find out if I'm a freak\mI go and I find the one and only answer every week\mAnd it's just me and all the memories to follow\mDown any course that fits within a fifty minute hour\mAnd we fathom all the mysteries, explicit and inherent\mWhen I hit a rut, she says to try the other parent\mAnd she's so kind, I think she wants to tell me something\mBut she knows that it's much better if I get it for myself\mAnd she says ooh oh, what do you hear in these sounds?\mAnd ooh oh, what do you hear in these sounds?\mI say, "I hear a doubt, with the voice of true believing\mAnd the promises to stay, and the footsteps that are leaving"\mAnd she says, "Oh," I say, "What," she says, "Exactly,"\mI say, "What, you think I'm angry, does that mean you think I'm angry?"\mShe says "Look, you come here every week\mWith jigsaw pieces of your past\mIt's all on little soundbites, and voices out of photographs\mAnd that's all yours, that's the guide, that's the So that was the first big weekend of the summer...\mStarts Thursday as usual with The Canteen quiz and again no-one wins the big cash prize\mLater I do my sound bloke routine by approaching Gina's new boyfriend to say that he shouldn't feel that there's any animosity between us and then I even go and make peace with her: shouldn't have bothered\mThen on Friday night we went through to the Arches\m...\mThere was only one car going so some of us had to get the train. We got through quite late. Then we went to a pub to \mtake the gear\mThere was no problems getting in - we saw some others waiting down the front of the queue so we skipped in\mIt was a good night - everyone was nutted and I ended up dancing with some blonde girl\mI thought she had been quite pretty until last night when Matthew informed me that she had, in fact, been a pig\mWhen the club finished we wandered the streets for a while until we got to this 24-hour cafe\mI didn't like the look of it so we left and got a taxi back to Morag's flat\mI couldn't sleep so I sat about drinking someone else's strawberry tonic wine and tried to keep everyone else up\mThen at ten o'clock in the morning we went downstairs to buy some drink\mWe had intended to watch the football in the afternoon but we'd passed out by then and slept right through it, awaking to find that England had won two-nil\mThen we went to get the train home and had a few in the station bar\mWe had some stuff left from the previous night's supplies so when we got home we decided to go down to John's indie disco\mSame story as Friday - lots of hugging, lots of dancing etc. etc\mI couldn't sleep again so went to the park to look at the toon, taking a detour through the \mplaypark\mTo get in we had to climb over a ten-foot steel fence, which resulted in severe bruising of our hands, legs and groins, but we had a good laugh on the stuff, especially the tube-slide, which probably doubles up as a urinal for drunk teens\mThen we walked through the woods to have a look at the tomb.\m Big disappointment, but the \mmist on the lake was cool\mSunday afternoon we go up to John's with a lot of beer in time to watch The Simpsons - it was a really good episode about love always ending in tragedy except, of course, for Marge and Homer. It was quite moving at the end and to tell you the truth my eyes were a bit damp\mThen we watched these young girls in swimsuits have a water fight in the street (You taping this, aye?)\mWe went up to the pub about ten\mIt was busy for a Sunday night, lots of people we know, including my first ever girlfriend who I still find very attractive, quite frankly, but I didn't really speak to her\mShe's probably still a bitch, anyway\mHer friend Gillian was there, I had a chat with her, she was still quite pleasant\mAt the same time I watched Malcolm make some terrible attempt to try and chat up a girl we know called Jo.\m He made some remark about her skirt that was barely there the previous night or something\mI couldn't sleep again that night, thanks to some seriously disturbing nightmares...Matthew says \mI should cut down on the cheese\m"went out for the weekend, it lasted for ever, high with our friends it's officially summer."\m"went out for the weekend, it lasted for ever, high with our friends it's officially summer."\m"went out for the weekend, it lasted for ever, high with our friends it's officially summer."\m"went out for the weekend, it lasted for ever, high with our friends it's officially summer."\m"went out for the weekend, it lasted for ever, high with our friends it's officially summer."\mI got some sleep eventually on Monday afternoon\mIt was a beautiful day, and later that evening Malcolm introduced me to the power of Merrydown - £1.79 a litre, 8.2% - mmmm.....\mJudith and Laura came round later and we sat in my back garden and drank\mThen Matthew came round and we went up the town\m"went out for the weekend, it lasted for ever, high with our friends yeah"\mIt's officially summer"went out for the weekend, it lasted for ever, high with our friends it's officially summer."

You just have to be sure you're doing the right thing. I mean it's very easy to forget - she was just sitting there in the pub with her new friends and her new life and her new hair, and it might have been five years but you'd know just to look at her\mI wasn't even sure it was her at first; I was ready to walk away but she smiled and called me over and we said hello for a bit. When we went back to our tables we were trying not to look over at each other and told our friends to stop staring. I didn't see her for the rest of the night, but by closing time the beer's kicked in so I go up and speak to her and we end up going for a walk, and talking about our new homes, our new jobs, our new friends, and our \mnew birds\mShe said she'd been going out with him now for about two and a half years, but they don't live together so he'd never find out. And you think about chasing her about school when you were wee and lying in your bed and listening to love songs and pretending they were about you. And the first time you asked her out she said no but one night you went to a wedding and when you came back to the pub she'd changed her mind and you went out. You remember the way she swung her arms when she held your hand but you can't remember how she kissed and now you've got the chance to find out\mBut you have to remember there's this other kiss and she's sittin' at home wondering where you are and what you're doing. And you worked hard on this kiss and you know it inside out; it's as much yours as it is hers, and it took a long time to get right, it took months of practice and months of embarrassment, but now you've got it perfected and you've been looking forward to that kiss all week\mYou can see her breath in the air between your faces, as you stand in the leaves and she just asks you straight out if you want to come and stay at her flat. But you make sure you get separate taxis and you go home and there might be a slight regret and maybe you'll wonder what you missed, but you have to remember the kiss that you worked so hard on. It's been a long and lonely trip\mBut I'm glad I took it because it was well worth it\mI got to read a couple books and do some research before I reached my verdict\mNever thought that I was perfect\mAlways thought that I had a purpose\mAnd I used to wonder if I'd live to see my first kiss\mThe most difficult thing that I did was recite my own words at a service\mRealizing the person I was addressing\mProbably wasn't looking down from heaven\mOr cooking up something in hell's kitchen\mTrying to listen in or eavesdrop from some another dimension\mIt was self-serving just like this is\mConveniently religious on Easter Sunday and on Christmas\mThe television went from being a babysitter to a mistress\mTechnology made it easy for us to stay in touch while keeping a distance\m'til we just stayed distant and never touched\mNow all we do is text too much\mI don't remember much from my youth\mMaybe my memory is repressed\mOr I just spent too much time wondering if I'd live to have sex\mFell in love for the first time in 4th grade\mBut I didn't have the courage to talk to her\mIn 8th grade I wrote her the note but I slipped it in someone else's locker\mConsidered killing myself because of that\mIt was a big deal\mIt was a blown cover\mIt was over for me\mMy goose was cooked\mStick a fork in me\mThe jig is up\mI blew my chances, the rest is history, our future was torn asunder\mIt became abundantly clear that I was only brought here to suffer\mAt least I didn't include my name\mThankfully I wrote the whole note in code and it had 10 layers\mOf scotch tape safety seal making it impossible to open\mPlus, it was set to self destruct\mWhoever read it probably died... laughing\mI wonder if they lived long enough to realize what happened\mA year later, I came to understand that wasn't love that I was feeling for her\mI had someone else to obsess over\mI was older\mAnd I was very mature\mI forged my time signature while practicing my parents autograph\mCause I was failing math\mDisconnected the phone when I thought the teacher would call my homeI checked the mailbox twice a day at the end of a long dirt road\mSteamed open a couple envelopes like I was in private detective mode\mIf you snoop around long enough for something in particular\mYou're guaranteed to find it\mFor better or worse that's how I learned\mThat it's best to just keep some things private\mIt was the best of times\mIt was the end of times\mIt was the best of times\mIt was the end of times\mI was always on deck, I was next in line\mAn only child with a pen and pad\mWriting a list of things that I could never have\mThe walls in my house were paper-thin\mEvery squabble seemed to get deafening\mIf my memory serves me correctly I made it a point to void and forget some things\mProbably to keep from being embarrassed\mNever meant to upset or give grief to my parents\mKept my secrets... hid my talents...\mIn my head, never under the mattress\mTherapy couldn't break me\mNever learned a word that would ensure safety\mSo I spoke softly and I tiptoed often\mThe door to my room was like a big old coffin\mThe way that it creaked when I closed it shut\mAnxieties peaked when it opened up\mAs if everything that I was thinking would be exposed\mI still sleep fully clothed\mIt was the best of timesIt was beautiful\mIt was brutal\mIt was cruel\mIt was business as usual\mHeaven\mIt was hell\mUsed to wonder if I'd live to see 12\mWhen I did I figured that I was immortal\mLoved to dance but couldn't make it to the formal\mCouldn't bear watching my imaginary girlfriend bust a move with any other dudes\mTone Loc was talking bout a "Wild Thang" but I was still caught up in some child thangs\mScared of a God who couldn't spare the rod\mIt was clearly a brimstone and fire thang\mPyromaniac\mKleptomaniac\mCouldn't explain my desire to steal that fire\mNow I add it to my rider\mLike "Please oh please don't throw me in that patch of brier!"\m It was the best of times\mIt was the end of times\mThe school counselor was clueless cause I never skipped classes\mPerfect attendance\mImperfect accent\mSpeech impediment they could never really fix and I faked bad eyesight so I could wear glasses\mConsidered doing something that would cripple me\mI wanted a wheelchair\mI wanted the sympathy\mI wanted straight teeth so then came braces\m4 years of headgear helped me change faces\mIt was the best of times\mIt was the end of times\mNow I wonder if I'll live to see marriage\mWonder if I'll live long enough to have kids\mWonder if I'll live to see my kids have kids\mIf I do I'm gonna tell 'em how it is\m"Don't listen when they tell you that these are your best years\mDon't let anybody protect your ears\mIt's best that you hear what they don't want you to hear\mIt's better to have pressure from peers than not have peers\mBeer won't give you chest hair\mSpicy food won't make it curl\mWhen you think you've got it all figured out and then everything collapses\mTrust me, kid\mIt's not the end of the world."

lyrics: So you did what you thought was right\mOh, giving up the fight\mThe only way that we knew was wrong\mGot me hanging on and on\mIt's everything you want\mAnd everything you need\mAnd the people who counted on\mLet you down, one by one\mSo be sure what you're asking for\mTelephone don't ring no more\mIt's everything you want\mAnd everything you need\mOoh, in the right crowd\mFace down in the right town\mNo good up to now, but maybe somehow\mWe'll get back home\mDon't care who walks through the door\mThe life I paid twice for\mRearranging the furniture\mReminds me of who you were\mIt's everything you want\mAnd everything you need\mOoh, in the right crowd\mFace down in the right town\mNo good up to now, well maybe somehow\mOoh, in the right crowd\mFace down in the right town\mNo good up to now, well maybe somehow\mWe'll get back home\mWe'll get back home\mWe'll get back home\mWe'll get back home

Le sol a glissé sous mes pas\mJe marche dans l'obscurité\mCette nuit, a sonné le glas\mOù je pleurerai pour l'éternité\mC'est cet endroit nommé le paradis\mQui me délaisse dans le noir\mC'est ce dieu qui m'a maudit\mQui me remplit de désespoir\mLes moines de ténébreuses pierres\mM'ont condamné pour un crime\mMais je pourrai traverser les enfers\mPour Marie, te revoir dans les cimes\mPourquoi marcher dans l'obscurité\mQuand je suis un ange blanc\mJe souhaiterais être vivant\mEt ne plus être l'ange damné\m(Translation)\m(Black Paradise)\mThe ground has slipped under my steps\mI am now walking in darkness\mThis night the bells tolled\mI shall cry for eternity\mIt is that place called Heaven\mThat leaves me alone in the dark\mIt is that God who cursed me\mThat fills me with despair\mThe monks of dark stones\mHave doomed me for a crime\mBut I could go through hell\mTo see you again, Marie, in the sky\mWhy should I wander through darkness\mWhen I am a white angel\mI wish I were still a human being\mAnd not that doomed angel \m(Translated from french by Pandora)

Je ne sais que faire de cette vie\mDans cet enfer au paradis\mJ'ai perdu mes ailes et ma liberté\mA cause de celle que j'ai tant t'aimé\mDes larmes de glace sont comme des espoirs\mLentement ils s'effacent de ma mémoire\mJ'aurais tant voulu ne jamais exister\mNi jamais avoir cru pouvoir aimer\mJ'ai tant de haine contre ceux qui ont\mCréé mes peines et mes passions\mJe crie de douleur, j'ai mal et j'ai peur\mJ'aimerais tant pouvoir encore la revoir\mJ'ai beau crier, elle ne m'entend pas\mJ'ai beau pleurer, elle ne m'aimera pas\m(Translation)\m(This Hell in Paradise)\mI do not know what to do with this life\mIn this hell in Paradise\mI lost my wings and my freedom\mBecause of the one I have been loving so much\mFrozen tears are like my hopes\mSlowly they fade from my memory\mI really wish I had not existed ever\mNor had thought I could love\mI feel so much hatred for those\mWho have created my griefs and passions\mI cry with pain, it hurts and I'm scared\mI wish I could see her again\mAlthough I am yelling, she's not hearing me\mAlthough I am crying, she's not loving me...(Translated from french by Pandora)

La tristesse éternelle d'un ange sur la terre\mDe grandes fontaines de larmes coulant Ã l'infini\mLes yeux noirs de cet être, fixant la pierre\mTombée d'une sculpture durant la nuit\mL'enfer a doucement touché notre sol\mMais de la mort il est si las\mQue même le paradis le désole\mMourir pour cet empire de glace ?\mDe roses est recouvert le tombeau\mQue foulera l'ange mélancolique\mSa main encore posée sur le berceau\mDe sa triste sculpture idyllique\m(Translation)\m(Amidst the Graves)\mThe eternal sadness of an angel on earth\mHuge fountains of tears flowing eternally\mThe black eyes of this being staring at the piece of stone\mFallen from a sculpture in the night\mHell has softly touched the ground\mBut of Death he is so tired\mThat even Paradise makes him sad\mAm I to die for that frozen empire ?\mRoses cover the tomb\mThat shall be trodden by the melancholic angel\mHis hand still on the cradle\mOf its sad idyllic sculpture\m(Translated from french by Pandora)

Des milliers d'âmes tombent du ciel\mEt les vies et les morts se mélangent\mLa terre s'est ouverte de part le cimetière\mÉbranlant les croix et les sépultures\mLes deux armées se sont unis par le feu\mAu milieu des brumes et des vents\mFaisant ainsi vaciller le monde\mDétruisant la vie et gavant la mort\mLes corps tombent du ciel \mDe sang chaud encore ruisselant\mComme pour nourrir la terre\mAffamée par tant de haine\mDe ces deux magnifiques royaumes\mPersonne ne viendra fêter la victoire\mLes anges et les démons sont morts\mDans les entrailles de ce purgatoire\m(Translation)\m(The Entrails of that Purgatory)\mThousands of souls fall from the sky\mLives and deaths blending\mThe ground opened in the cemetery\mShaking crosses and graves\mThe two armies have been united by fire\mIn the mist and the winds\mMaking thus the world falter\mDestroying Life and cramming Death\mCorpses fall from Heaven\mFull of warm blood still streaming out\mAs if to feed the land\mStarved by so much hatred\mOf those two magnificent realms\mNo one will celebrate the victory\mAngels and demons are dead\mIn the entrails of that purgatory\m(Translated from french by Pandora)

trackname: If I Could Be Where You Are
lyrics: [Verse 1]\mWhere are you this moment?\mOnly in my dreams\mYou're missing, but you're always\mA heartbeat from me\m[Verse 2]\mI'm lost now without you\mI don't know where you are\mI keep watching, I keep hoping\mBut time keeps us apart\m[Chorus 1]\mIs there a way I can find you?\mIs there a sign I should know?\mIs there a road I could follow\mTo bring you back home?\m[Verse 3]\mWinter lies before me\mNow you're so far away\mIn the darkness of my dreaming\mThe light of you will stay\m[Chorus 2]\mIf I could be close beside you\mIf I could be where you are\mIf I could reach out and touch you\mAnd bring you back home\m[Chorus 1]\mIs there a way I can find you?\mIs there a sign I should know?\mIs there a road I can follow\mTo bring you back home to me?

[Verse 1]\mStrange how my heart beats\mTo find myself upon your shore\mStrange how I still feel\mMy loss of comfort gone before\m[Verse 2]\mCool waves wash over\mAnd drift away with dreams of youth\mSo time is stolen\mI cannot hold you long enough\m[Bridge]\mAnd so this is where I should be now\mDays and nights falling by\mDays and nights falling by me\mI know of a dream I should be holding\mDays and nights falling by\mDays and nights falling by me\m[Verse 3]\mSoft blue horizons\mReach far into my childhood days\mAs you are rising\mTo bring me my forgotten ways\m[Verse 4]\mStrange how I falter\mTo find I'm standing in deep water\mStrange how my heart beats\mTo find I'm standing on your shore

[Verse 1]\mCold as the northern winds\mIn December mornings\mCold is the cry that rings\mFrom this far distant shore\m[Verse 2]\mWinter has come too late\mToo close beside me\mHow can I chase away\mAll these fears deep inside?\m[Chorus]\mI'll wait the signs to come\mI'll find a way\mI will wait the time to come\mI'll find a way home\m[Verse 3]\mMy light shall be the moon\mAnd my path - the ocean\mMy guide the morning star\mAs I sail home to you\m[Chorus]\mI'll wait the signs to come\mI'll find a way\mI will wait the time to come\mI'll find a way home\m[Verse 4]\mWho then can warm my soul?\mWho can quell my passion?\mOut of these dreams - a boat\mI will sail home to you

[Verse 1]\mYou say I made you fall in love with me\mWish I could make you fall in love with you\mYou believed in the magic that us could be\mAnd what that you and I means one could do\mEvery instinct you had said run from me\mThat this newfound touch is uncomfortable\mAnd to truly stand naked in front of me\mOr yourself for that then matter is something new\mI take no pride knowing that\mYou avoid the mirror to shun what you despise\mNever knew the beauty you came here with\mTill the first time you caught your reflection in my eyes\mNever you mind what I see in you\mGrow because you're beautiful, not because I need you to\mGrow till you outstretch every single piece of you\mHeaven will see you through but you got to believe it's true\mGo write your story\mEven if in the end you might outgrow me\mI'll always treasure the chapter that was mine\mAnd twist through time with a smile knowing you're free\m[Hook]\mPuppy love is real to a puppy\mI still want to feel you touch me\mI'm not saying leave me, please just be free\mI love you so much, I don't want you to need me\mPuppy love's real to a puppy\mI still want to feel you up under me\mNot saying leave me, please just be free\mI love you so much, I don't want you to need me\m[Verse 2]\mThe sky all alone is glorious\mWe behold it but we can't hold it up\mWhen god says that's it and hits the switch\mIt'll all come tumbling down when it's bored with us\mSweet you and all your radiance\mI can please you, but I can't save you sis\mI adore you and might even open up\mBut even I can't love you enough for both of us\mCan't hold you close enough\mCan't enter the holes you've boarded up\mClose your eyes, concentrate on my voice\mWant to make your love for me pure, make it a choice\m[Hook][Break x2]\mThe sky is there to behold\mYou just want to be held when you're cold\mJust grow, stretch out your soul\mAnd if you still want me I'll watch you grow old

[Verse 1]\mWill I ever get to, to where it is that I am going?\mWill I ever follow through with what I, with what I had planned?\mI guess it's possible that I have been a bit distracted\mAnd the directions for me are a lot less in demand\mIn demand\m[Chorus]\mWill I ever get to where I'm going?\mIf I do, will I know when I'm there?\mIf the wind blew me in the right direction, yeah\mWould I even care?\m[Post-Chorus]\mI would\m[Verse 2]\mI take a look around, it's evident the scene has changed\mAnd there are times when I feel improved, improved upon the past\mThen there are times when I can't seem to understand at all\mAnd yes it seems as though I'm going nowhere really fucking fast\mNowhere fast\m[Chorus]\mWill I ever get to where I'm going?\mIf I do, will I know when I'm there?\mIf the wind blew me in the right direction, yeah\mWould I even care?\m[Post-Chorus]\mI would\mI would\mI would\m[Chorus]\mWill I ever get to where I'm going?\mIf I do, will I know when I'm there?\mIf the wind blew me in the right direction, yeah\mWould I even care?\m[Outro]\mI would\mI would\mI would\mI would\mI would

There you go\mFlashing fever from your eyes\mHey baby\mCome over here and shut them tight\mI'm not denying\mWe're flying above it all\mHold my hand\mDon't let me fall\mYou've such amazing grace\mI've never felt this way\mOhhh, show me heaven\mCover me\mLeave me breathless\mOhh show me heaven please x3\mHere I go\mI'm shaking just like the breeze\mHey baby\mI need your hand to steady me\mI'm not denying\mI'm frightened as much as you\mThough I'm barely touching you\mI've shivers down my spine and it feels divine\mOhh show me heaven\mCover me\mLeave me breathless\mOhh show me heaven please\mDo you know what its like to dream a dream\mBaby hold me tight and let this be\mOhh show me heaven\mCover me\mLeave me breathless\mOhh show me heaven please\mFade chorus

Walk blindly to the light and reach out for his hand\mDon't ask any questions and don't try to understand\mOpen up your mind and then open up your heart\mAnd you will see that you and me aren't very far apart\m'Cause I believe that love is the answer\mI believe that love will find the way\mViolence is spread worldwide and there's families on-the street\mAnd we sell drugs to children now oh why can't we just see\mThat all we do is eliminate our future with the things we do today\mMoney is our incentive now so that makes it okay\mBut I believe that love is the answer\mI believe that love will find the way\mI believe that love is the answer\mI believe that love will find the way\mOoooh\mI've been seeing Lisa now for a little over a year\mShe said she's never been so happy but Lisa lives in fear\mThat one day daddy's gonna find out she's in love\mWith a nigga from the streets\mOh how he would lose it then but she's still here with me\m'Cause she believes that love will see it through\mAnd one day he'll understand\mAnd he'll see me as a person and not just a black man\m'Cause I believe that love is the answer\mI believe that love will find the way\mI believe I believe I believe I believe that love is the answer\mI believe that love will find the way\mLove will find the way (x7)

trackname: Always Coming Back Home To You
lyrics: To all my killers and my hundred dollar billers\mTo emo kids that got too many feelings\mHe held the register open while he counted her change\mI was next in line which meant I was invisible\mFrom where I stood I could see that the till was full\mHe didn't look the type to play superhero\mSo I stepped forth and paid for my cigarettes\mCrept out the store's front door to chase a little breath\mBangles in my head, shake the song off\mAnother manic Monday night, its gonna be a long walk\mA car pulled up, a fixed up Cutlass\mA woman and a child climbed out and left it running\mThey went inside of the deli, placed an order\mWith the extra dollar fifty bottled water cause the daughter's picky\mWhen they came out mommy gave me a glance\mThat said man can love an angel but he's got to take the chance\mAlready knew the deal, I lit one up and walked\mSo they got back in they Oldsmobile, belted up, and took off\mThug love on the corner by the Walgreens\mLooking at me like I'm just another square Saltine\mAs I get closer I notice they showing each other sketches\mOut of their notebooks, reminded me of my old roots\mI walk past with a nod and a reminisce\mSwear to god hip hop and comic books was my genesis\mRespect the life and the fashions of the children\mIt's the only culture I've got, exactly what we've been building\mAll of a sudden I'm in front of some man\mNo, he's a young'un, but he's got a gun in his hand\mHe looks fifteen, he looks frantic, no, he looks afraid\mImmediately apprehensive 'til I heard him say\m"Do you want this? It's not mine, I promise\mI found it on my block in between a couple garages\mDidn't want to leave it for a child to stumble over\mI don't even know how to hold it"\mIt was a thirty eight, the poor man's machete\mHeld it in my hand, thinking damn man it's heavier than expected\mWedged it behind my belt buckle\mKnowing that it's evil, even thought that I could smell trouble\mThe extra strength felt weak\mBut over there on the corner saw what I needed\mAnd proceeded to cross the street\mPut the heat in the mail box to lose it\mFigured that the post office knows what's best to do with itMosey down the road, thinking about the old\mI used to roam this zone through two feet of snow\mRight here, this used to be a record shop\mI've gotten love, I've gotten drunk, I've gotten beat up in that parking lot\mI've had my Lake Street pride for 3 decades\mThese alleyways, and these streetlights have seen my best days\mBefore I was a germ learning how to misbehave\mAll the way to the grave, south side is my resting place\mTook a right on Lyndale I'm getting near\mBut then the road became empty and the people disappeared\mThe clouds ran away, opened up the sky\mAnd one by one I watched every constellation die\mAnd there I was frozen, standing in my backyard\mFace to face, eye to eye, staring at the last star\mI should've known, walked all the way home\mTo find that she wasn't here, I was still all alone\mNo matter where I am, no matter what I do\mI'm always coming back home to you\mThey can leave me for dead they can take away my true\mI'm always coming back home to you\mThrough the lies and the sins that ride the wind that blew\mI'm always coming back home to you\mAs sure as the life in the garden that you grew\mI'm always coming back home to you\mNo matter where I am, no matter what I do\mI'm always coming back home to you\mIf only I had known what you already knew\mI'm always coming back home to you\mFrom the heaven I've had to the hell I been through\mI'm always coming back home to you\mI'm always coming back home to you

Days like these could never last\mWould I find you with a net outcast\mPour a glass brimful of red\mDrink it down the past is dead\mTraveling over  land and sea\mWandering soul hear my plea\mCover your eyes the moment's due\mIt moves so fast what's left that's new?\mWhen autumn comes around again\mRemember me your truest friend\mTraveling over  land and sea\mWandering soul hear my plea\mEye to eye and word for word\mTime slipped out with the early bird\mThe ripening fruit's a deep shade of red\mI'll keep some back for the road ahead

[Verse 1]\mDon't care what they have to say\mNo point in listening to them anyway\mWhy do you have to give them what they want?\mThey love to watch you as you fall apart\m[Chorus]\mStick it to them like a phoenix rise\mThere's nothing grander than the big surprise\mThey can't hurt you with their sticks and stones\mAbout time take them right between the eyes\m[Verse 2]\mSeek to destroy cause they're scared of you\mThat's why they try to make a fool of you\mThey're so jealous of my pretty star\m'Cause you've got soul inside your shattered heart\m[Chorus]\mStick it to them like a phoenix rise\mThere's nothing grander than the big surprise\mThey can't hurt you with their sticks and stones\mAbout time take them right between the eyes\m[Breakdown]\mAnd you've been waiting all your life\mTo fly high into somebody else\mAnd it's true it's a cruel, cruel world\mLife's a bitch and then you die, my love\m[Verse 3]\mDon't care what they have to say\mYou shouldn't listen to them anyway\m[Chorus]\mStick it to them like a phoenix rise\mThere's nothing grander than the big surprise\mThey can't hurt you with their sticks and stones\mAbout time take them right between the eyes\m[Interlude]\mPeople like to build you up\mThen they'll stab you in the back like that\mYou know it breaks my heart\mCan't see you going out like that[Outro]\mStay alive, my love\mStay alive, my love\mStay alive, my love\mStay alive, my love

[Verse 1]\mAvalanche is sullen and too thin\mShe starves herself to rid herself of sin\mAnd the kick is so divine when she sees bones beneath her skin\mAnd she says:\m[Chorus]\mHey baby, can you bleed like me?\mC'mon baby, can you bleed like me?\m[Verse 2]\mChris is all dressed up and acting coy\mPainted like a brand new Christmas toy\mHe's trying to figure out if he's a girl or he's a boy\mAnd he says:\m[Chorus]\mHey baby, can you bleed like me?\mC'mon baby, can you bleed like me?\m[Instrumental break]\m[Verse 3]\mDoodle takes dad's scissors to her skin\mAnd when she does relief comes setting in\mWhile she hides the scars she's making underneath her pretty clothes\mShe sings:\m[Chorus]\mHey baby, can you bleed like me?\mC'mon baby, can you bleed like me?\m[Verse 4]\mTherapy is Speedie's brand new drug\mDancing with the devil's past has never been too fun\mIt's better off than trying to take a bullet from a gun\mAnd she cries:\m[Chorus]\mHey baby, can you bleed like me?\mC'mon baby, can you bleed like me?[Instrumental break]\m[Verse 5]\mJ.T. gets all fucked up in some karaoke bar\mAfter two drinks he's a loser, after three drinks he's a star\mGetting all nostalgic as he sings "I Will Survive"\m[Chorus]\mHey baby, can you bleed like me?\mC'mon baby, can you bleed like me?\mHey baby, can you bleed like me?\mOh, c'mon baby, can you bleed like me?\m[Breakdown]\mYou should see my scars\mYou should see my scars\mYou should see my scars\mYou should see my scars\mTry to comprehend that which you'll never comprehend\mTry to comprehend that which you'll never comprehend\mJust try to comprehend that which you'll never comprehend\mTry to comprehend that which you'll never comprehend\m[Outro]\m(You should see my scars)\mLa la la\mLa la la\m(You should see my scars)\mLa la la\mLa la la

trackname: You Don't Know What Love Is
lyrics: You don't know what love is\mUntil you've learned the meaning of the blues\mUntil you've loved a love you had to lose\mYou don't know what love is\mYou don't know how lips hurt\mUntil you've kissed and had to pay the cost\mUntil you've flipped your heart and you have lost\mYou don't know what love is\mDo you know how lost hearts fear\mThe thought of reminiscing\mAnd how lips tasting of tears\mLose the taste for kissing\mYou don't know how hearts yearn\mFor love that cannot live yet never dies\mUntil you've faced each dawn with sleepless eyes\mHow could you know what love is

Everyone dated the demise of our neighborhood\mFrom the suicides of the Lisbon girls\mPeople saw their clairvoyance in the wiped out elms\mAnd the harsh sunlight\mSome thought the tortures tearing the Lisbon girls\mPointed to a simple refusal to accept the world\mAs it was handed down to them\mSo full of flaws\mBut the only thing we are certain of\mAfter all these years\mIs the insufficiency of explanation\m(Obviously, doctor, you've never been a 13 year old girl)\mThe Lisbon girls were\mThirteen, Cecilia\mFourteen, Lux\mFifteen, Bonnie\mSixteen, Mary\mAnd seventeen, Therese\mNo one could understand how\mMrs. Lisbon and Mr. Lisbon\mOur math teacher\mHad produced such beautiful creatures\mFrom that time on\mThe Lisbon house began to change\mAlmost everyday\mAnd even when she wasn't keeping an eye on Cecilia\mLux would suntan on a towel\mWearing a swimsuit that caused the knife sharpener\mTo give her a 15 minute demonstration for free\mThe only reliable boy who got to know Lux\mWas Trip Fontaine\mWho only 18 months before the suicides\mHad emerged from baby fat\mTo the delight of girls and mothers alike\mBut few anticipated it would be so drastic\mThe girls were pulled out of school\mAnd Mrs Lisbon shut the house in maximum security isolation\mThe girls' only contact with the outside world\mWas through the catalogs they ordered\mThat started to fill the Lisbon's mailbox\mWith pictures of high-end fashions and brochures for exotic vacations\mUnable to go anywhere\mThe girls traveled in their imaginations\mTo gold tipped Siamese temples, or past an old man with a leaf broom\mTiding a moss-carpeted speck of Japan\mAnd Cecilia hadn't died\mShe was a bride in Calcutta\mCollecting everything we could of theirs\mWe couldn't get the Lisbon girls out of our minds\mBut they were slipping away\mThe colours of their eyes were fading\mAlong with exact locations of moles and dimplesFrom five they had become four\mAnd they were all living in the dead\mBecoming shadows\mWe would have lost them completely\mIf the girls hadn't contacted us\mLux was the last to go\mFleeing from the house we had forgot to stop at the garage\mAfter the suicide free-for-all\mMr and Mrs. Lisbon gave up any attempt to lead a normal life\mThey had Mr Hedly pack up the house\mSelling what furniture he could in a garage sale\mEveryone went just to look\mOur parents did not buy used furniture\mAnd they certainly didn't buy furniture tainted by death\mWe, of course, took the family photos that were put out with the trash\mMr. Lisbon put the house on the market\mAnd it was sold to a young couple from Boston\mIt didn't matter in the end how old they had been\mOr that they were girls\mBut only that we had loved them\mAnd they hadn't heard us calling..still do not hear us\mCalling them out of those rooms\mWhere they went to be alone for all time\mAlone in suicide\mWhich is deeper then death\mAnd where we will never find the pieces\mTo put them back together

lyrics: [Verse 1]\mWell, I got shot right in the back\mAnd you were there, you were there\mI said I was never coming back\mAnd you were there, you were there\mWell I know the eyelids are under attack\mYou were there, you were there\mWell, it's like the pressure wants to retract\mBecause you were there, you were there\m[Chorus]\mAnd if God is what they made\mCut their hands off believers\mDon't get high on what you create\m[Verse 2]\mWell, I saw Gaza turn into light\mAnd you were there, you were there\mAll the subtractions made it on time\mBecause you were there, you were there\mWell, all the nice boys wait for a sign\mYou were there, you were there\mWhen I was out on the town, the town\mAnd I needed it, needed it\m[Chorus]\mAnd if love is what they gave\mTurn wives into healers\mDon't get high on what you create\mOr it might just steal ya
